#: ../../manual/modeling/metas/introduction.rst:13
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Meta objects are *implicit surfaces*, meaning that they are *not explicitly* "
"defined by vertices (as meshes are) or control points (as surfaces are): they "
"exist *procedurally*. Meta objects are literally mathematical formulas that "
"are calculated on-the-fly by Blender."
msgstr ""
"融球属于implicit surfaces隐式曲面，意思是它们 不是 像网格物体那样明确地 由顶点"
"来定义形状，也不是像表面那样由控制点来定义形状：它们是procedurally程序化的存"
"在。Meta（数元）从字面上的理解就是：由Blender动态计算的mathematical "
"formulas（数学公式）。 "

#: ../../manual/modeling/metas/introduction.rst:18
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"A very distinct visual characteristic of metas is that they are fluid "
"*mercurial*, or *clay-like* forms that have a \"rounded\" shape. Furthermore, "
"when two meta objects get close to one another, they begin to interact with "
"one another. They \"blend\" or \"merge\", as water droplets do, especially in "
"zero-g (which, by the way, makes them very handy for modeling streams of water "
"when you do not want to do a fluid simulation). If they subsequently move away "
"from one another, they restore their original shape."
msgstr ""
"融球有一个非常与众不同的视觉特征：它们有善变的流体性、粘土状的组合、“圆滑”的外"
"形。此外，当两个融球接近彼此时，它们会产生相互作用。它们会“混合”或者“聚合”，就"
"像水滴一样，尤其是在零重力状态下。（其中，随便说一下，当你不想用物理仿真来做流"
"体时，可以用融球很方便地为流水建模。） 如果两个融球它们后来又被彼此分离，那么它"
"们将恢复各自原本的形状。 "

#: ../../manual/modeling/metas/introduction.rst:25
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Each of these is defined by its own underlying mathematical structure (:doc:`/"
"modeling/metas/structure`), and you can at any time switch between them using "
"the *Active Element* panel."
msgstr ""
"每个融球都由它自己相关的mathematical structure数学结构所定义，你可以在任何时间"
"在Active Element活动元素面板里切换它们。 "

#: ../../manual/modeling/metas/introduction.rst:28
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Typically *Meta* objects are used for special effects or as a basis for "
"modeling. For example, you could use a collection of metas to form the initial "
"shape of your model and then convert it to a mesh for further modeling. Meta "
"objects are also very efficient for ray-tracing."
msgstr ""
"融球通常用于特技效果或作为建模的基础。例如，您可以用一批融球的集合作为模型的初"
"始形状，然后把它们转换为其它物体类型，以用于进一步的模型构造。（好吧，其实只能"
"转换为网格物体……）融球也能非常高效地应用于ray-tracing射线追踪。 "

#: ../../manual/modeling/metas/introduction.rst:34
#, fuzzy
